<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="170" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,430,635]" pageId="3" pageNumber="170">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1325789752" collectorName="Diagnosis. A" location="Central" pageId="3" pageNumber="170" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Central">
<collectorName box="[199,350,466,491]" pageId="3" pageNumber="170">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,466,491]" pageId="3" pageNumber="170">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A
</collectorName>
hemicytherid, subrectangular in lateral view with a delicate posteroventral caudal process. Eye spot pronounced. Anterior margin with an anterodorsal flange in LV. Surface ornamented with tubercles, mostly of them slightly aligned in rows. Hinge holamphidont with median element smooth and the posterior one bilobate. 
<collectingRegion box="[259,344,574,599]" country="Solomon Islands" name="Central" pageId="3" pageNumber="170">Central</collectingRegion>
muscle scars an oblique row of four adductors, the middle two subdivided; two frontal scars. Inner margin with a delicate anterior vestibule. Radial pore canals straight, simple and numerous.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/166662/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="170" targetBox="[167,1405,701,1030]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1435,1064,1117]" pageId="3" pageNumber="170">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,269,1064,1086]" pageId="3" pageNumber="170">FIGURE 2</emphasis>
. Pattern of central muscle scars of 
